ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Excluding equine influenza and equine herpesvirus will leave a list
of other infectious, febrile disease agents to be (serologically)
screened. Hopefully, the event will not remain unsolved.
According to an October 2005 decision of the International Olympic
Committee, the 2008 Olympic and Paralympic Equestrian Events have
been relocated from Beijing to Hong Kong. The considerations for the
said decision included Hong Kong's extensive experience in horse
racing, its status in equine health, and its world renowned
regulatory framework for equine diseases.- Mod.AS]
